++# Owner-Op Road Ready v96.6.0
++
++## Split sleeper berth clocks
++- Implements the property-carrying split sleeper provision for two qualifying rest periods.
++- Neither period may be under 2 consecutive hours.
++- One period must contain at least 7 consecutive hours in Sleeper Berth.
++- The two periods must total at least 10 hours.
++- Supports long-first and short-first pair order.
++- Recalculates the 11-hour and 14-hour clocks from the end of the first period.
++- Excludes the paired qualifying rest period from the 14-hour calculation.
++- Keeps the 30-minute break and 70/8 cycle clocks active.
++- Shows a pending/provisional split when the first period is complete and tells the driver the exact partner time still required.
++- Allows comparison with standard clocks from Drive Mode.
++- Current-day graph violation ranges use the pending split interpretation; completed past-day pairs are evaluated as completed splits.
++
++## Latest manual edit wins
++- An explicit event-time edit replaces every older event overlapped by the edited interval.
++- Immediate neighbors reconnect to the edited start/end boundary.
++- Older covered rows do not reappear after Save/reopen.
++
++## Preserved
++- Pre-trip is requested only after a true 10-hour OFF/SB reset, never merely at midnight.
++- Pickup BOL and Going to remain stored on the exact ON DUTY Pickup / Loading event.
++- Historical event locations, signing, cycle totals, and route metadata remain day/event scoped.
++
++## Verification
++- `verify-split-sleeper-v966.mjs`
++- `verify-latest-edit-authoritative-v966.mjs`
++- Existing v95.81 HOS, v95.89 violation graph, v96.4 route/BOL, and v96.5 pre-trip regression tests.
